title: Voodoo
overview:
Voodoo
    
        Play Voodoo demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Black cats and voodoo dolls haunt this slot machine. Keep an eye out for Baron Samedi and let the game bewitch you.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The theme of Voodoo is writ large in the title. Voodoo, or Vodun, is a range of religions that combine elements of West African religion with colonial Christianity. It branched out through the Americas thanks to the Atlantic slave trade and became a subject of much fascination in Western pop culture.
This is the well from which Voodoo the slot machine draws, with the image of Baron Samedi, a top hat wearing skeletal supernatural being whose image you may remember being prominent in Live and Let Die.
It is a nice, horror-inflected theme for a slot from Endorphina with cobwebbed symbols and Vodun related artworks.

media.caption: Simple win in the Voodoo slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics on this slot are gorgeous. Plenty of time has been spent rendering even the Ace to Ten symbols in a tone appropriate to the slot as a whole.
The murky green background evokes the modern colouration of horror films and the animations and sound design follow that queue with each symbol giving of eerie noises when you win with it.
The music is a funky blend of rattling bones, sliding scales and low bass beats that suggest the Carribean and horror equally. The music also regularly changes tones in a way that keeps it from becoming annoying the way most loops do.

Gameplay.text:
Voodoo is a five reel slot machine with ten winlines and three rows.
There is a simple gamble feature in which you choose a card which must be higher than the dealer's to win. While this appears to be a 50-50 prospect on the face of it, the reality is that the cards are not drawn without bias. As a result, the average return to player for the gamble feature is just 84%.
There is a simple bonus game to spice this up, but it is, on the whole, a fairly basic game from a features standpoint.

media.caption: Big win from free spins bonus feature
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Voodoo has a single special symbol. This Scatter serves as a Wild in the main game, standing in for any other symbol to make winning combinations.
It also pays out two times your bet per spin for hitting three of them on one spin. You then get twenty times your bet per spin for four symbols and two hundred for five.
On top of this three or more Scatters trigger ten free spins. During these free spins, the Scatter does not substitute for other symbols, instead, any symbol that is part of a winning combination expands to fill its reel and winnings are recalculated.

media.caption: 3 Scatter hits reward you with 10 free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.00%. This is around what we estimate to be the industry average.
However, if you play the Gamble feature the return to player in that is just 84% making this a bad option for those who like to use the gamble feature to up the volatility of a game which in this case is already high.
The range of bet on the site we tested was $/£/€0.01 per spin with just one line up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 if you play all ten lines on the highest possible number of coins and coin size.

media.caption: Different take on the gamble feature in Voodoo slot

Conclusion.text:
Voodoo is a gorgeous slot with some lovely sound design. The overall surface gloss is backed up by a solid set of features which, though simple, are satisfying.
The high variance works well with our strategies and the RTP, though not great, is well within our acceptable range.
This is a recommendation from us.

title: Northern Sky
overview:
Northern Sky
    
        Play Northern Sky demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Put your parka on and find your compass to head into the snowy wasteland with Northern Sky. Up there you’ll find beautiful visions, an RTP of 96.57% and a decent level of variance.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The aurora borealis, or Northern Lights, are a well known phenomenon that occurs as one gets closer and closer to the Arctic. Northern Sky uses this to create a stellar backdrop for its crystalline symbols. Bears, Caribou, Snowy Owls and Wolves inhabit the reels, rendered in a gorgeous diamond-esque style.
In the background a mountain rises towering out of snowy forests and the stars twinkle waiting for the bonus feature to trigger, bringing with it the aurora in all its colourful glory.

media.alt: Northern Sky slot Bonus game re-spin
media.caption: Hit at least one new symbol on any winline and you are guaranteed a respin

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The slot is a near perfect demonstration of how to build the visual and sound elements of a slot. The theme is strong, clear, and present in every visual detail. The symbols are beautiful and detailed, but also have strong silhouettes that make for easy-to-read reels at all magnifications.
The animations are simple but pretty, and they are timed to elicit that little bit of extra excitement when you land a win, or just miss a bonus symbol.
The sound, too, is well designed, building in time with the action and really drawing the player in.

media.caption: Bigger cumulative wins are failry usual in the bonus round

Gameplay.text:
Northern Sky is played on five reels with three rows and nine win lines.
Any winning combination pays out and then locks that combination in place for a free respin. Respins continue until no further winning combinations occur. The winnings are then paid out and the round ends.

media.caption: Gameplay video featuring free spins bonus game

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
There is no Wild symbol in Northern Sky.
The Bonus feature is triggered when three bonus symbols land anywhere and at any time in one round (a round includes free respins). The Bonus round consists of ten free spins with only the high paying animal symbols on the reels.

media.caption: If you are lucky, you'll collect scatter symbols throughout the respin rounds

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.57%, slightly over our yardstick of 96.00%.
The volatility of this game is medium to high, allowing it to pair decently well with our preferred strategies.
Since the bets are not made on a "per win line" basis the range of bet on the site we tested went from the minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 all the way up to a maximum bet per spin of $/£/€100.00. This is a very satisfying spread of bets.

media.caption: Northern Sky - top paying symbols
Northern Sky - low paying symbols in the base game

Conclusion.text:
Northern Sky does a fantastic job at the visual level. Luckily, this is also backed up under the hood, with excellent pacing and a respin mechanic that makes every win feel like a bonus round.
The return to player is above average and the volatility is within the kind of range we feel happy recommending.
Overall this is a great slot that we recommend to our readers wholeheartedly.

title: Genie Jackpots Megaways
overview:
Genie Jackpots Megaways

about_game: While we would use one of our three wishes to boost Genie Jackpot Megaways’s volatility, otherwise this is a pretty solid slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Genie Jackpot Megaways cashes in on the popularity of Walt Disney’s Aladdin, without awkwardly bumping up against the Mouse’s copyright claims.
As a result, this Genie doesn’t have the charms of Robin Williams’s extraordinary voice performance, but if you get lucky he does grant your wishes. Providing your wish is a reasonable return to player.
The slightly gaudy style works well with the ersatz Arabian stylings of the slot and the atmosphere it generates is as otherworldly as any of Sheherezade’s 1,001 tales.

media.caption: Jinn-credible win in the Genie Jackpot Megaways slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Whether the player buys into this slot will depend on whether the somewhat odd visual tone works for them. The colour palette is lifted from the more magical sections of Disney’s opus, but the actual style of the slot doesn’t quite match.
The result is something that looks a little spraypaint mural-like, which can look cheap or pleasing as per the player’s personal taste.
The music is well-chosen, although it is put thoroughly front and centre of the stage and so may irritate players faster than a more ambient track would.
The rest of the sound design and animations are solid, working to create a unified and polished feel. Unfortunately, that polish is on a plastic lamp, rather than a golden one.

Gameplay.text:
The 'Megaways' in the title of this slot indicates that it uses the Megaways system. This puts together any way wins style of calculating win lines and a randomised number of symbols (between two and five) on each of the six reels.
Any way wins means that wins occur for matching symbols in adjacent reels, running from reel one to the right, no matter where on the adjacent reels those symbols fall.
As a result, the number of ways to win varies from 64 up to 15,625.
Coupled with the random features and the multiple bonuses (details below), there is plenty to engage the player in this slot. There are four random features which add either additional winning symbols or additional wilds to the reels.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol, and appears on all reels except for reel one.
Hitting three or more Scatters results in a payout and triggers the Free Spin Bonus.
Three Scatter Symbols on the reels reward the player with ten free spins, four Scatter Symbols give the player twelve free spins, five Scatter Symbols award fifteen free spins, and six Scatter Symbols result in twenty free spins.
The Free Spin Bonus starts with the player choosing one of four lamps, each lamp having a feature behind it. The chosen feature is active during the subsequent free spins.
The four features are:
Impatient players can buy directly into the Bonus features for one hundred times the line bet.

media.alt: Genie Jackpot Megaways free spins win
media.caption: Free Spins win in the Genie Jackpot Megaways slot

media.alt: Genie Jackpot Megaways free spins options
media.caption: Choosing a lamp activates one of four features for the Free Spin Bonus

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.52%, a good chunk over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€10.00 per spin. This is an oddly low range but other casinos may offer a better spread. As is, that range should work for all low and medium stakes players, even if the high rollers are left out in the cold.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility in the slots we chose.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Genie Jackpot Megaways slot machine

Conclusion.text:
While visually somewhat kitsch, Genie Jackpots Megaways is a well-made piece of kit. The gameplay and bonuses are fun and varied and it sports a pretty decent RTP of 96.52%.
Unfortunately, it doesn’t work with our slot machine strategies, but for players who don’t mind the medium level volatility, this could be a good choice.

Theme and Storyline.text:
King Kong has fascinated the world since Edgar Wallace invented the colossal ape back in 1933. This version of him puts a crown on his head and a hawaiian shirt on his back. The art style suggests that there might be more influence from the Nintendo owned gorilla Donkey Kong rather than the cinematic giant.
He’s certainly got a more chill look at the top of the Empire State Building than the beast who is ultimately killed by beauty and a squadron of biplanes. Though the biplanes still make an appearance.
There’s plenty of great apes in the realm of slots, but only one is King.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are one of the major draws of this slot. The character of Kong is a cheery character snoozing beside the reels, ready to jump up and award the player a feature. His animations are crisp 3D renderings.
The reels themselves are adorned with a range of interesting symbols. The animals all come with kooky outfits, while the ace to ten symbols are in bold colours that jump out as they spin.
The sound scape is a little more limited than you’d expect from a slot with this much visual flare. But it does a good enough job of generating atmosphere. And it does so without overdoing it and becoming invasive or annoying.

Gameplay.text:
The base game is a five reel slot with three rows per reel and twenty win lines.
To spice things up, there are randomly triggered features that can affect any given spin. When the features are triggered, King Kong jumps up and activates the feature himself. These features include things like respins or additional wilds.
There is a range of bonus features as well, but no gamble feature. Though with everything else in play, you probably won’t miss a simple game of double-or-nothing too much.

title: Hoot Loot
overview:
Hoot Loot
    
        Play Hoot Loot demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: This low RTP (95%), medium volatility slot offers some cute animals, but little else.

Theme and Storyline.text:
This slot is themed around whimsical forest animals.
Set in a dark forest, players will be in the company of a range of furry friends, from a sleepy-looking porcupine to a friendly moose.
Other symbols include glowing mushrooms, paw prints and – of course – the charming owl eyes of the Hoot Loot. The mood is mischievous, as if the animals won’t quite give a straight answer when asked the way out of the forest.
The vibe will remind players of classic children’s cartoons, and they’ll definitely want to be in a youthful headspace to play.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
A series of cheerful notes play as the reels spin. When players win, a series of whimsical cartoon sound effects zing. This feels right on theme, though players who aren’t in the mood for the sugary music may wish to turn the sound off.
The animation of the cartoon animals brings to mind the style of Looney Tunes. With bulging eyes and impish expressions, they seem good natured and silly.
The evergreen trees that surround the reels reinforce the sense that players are in the depths of a forest. The starry sky above adds a festive feeling, as if everyone is up a little past their bedtime.

media.caption: Big win in the Hoot Loot slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Hoot Loot is a five reel, three row slot, with 20 win lines.
The gameplay is quite classic, and players will find what they expect with the exception of some bonus details (see below).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
The Scatter symbol appears only on reels 1, 3, and 5.
The Scatter symbol also initiates the Hoo’s Safe Bonus. During this feature, players may choose a Scatter symbol to reveal a reward. Every reward will be 5-25 times the player's initiating bet. The feature concludes when there are no picks remaining.
Players receive the win sum of the credits awarded at the end of the features.
The Hoot Line Feature is a separate bonus payline. It is made up of Hoot Line symbols which may be in any location on the reels (from left to right).
The Hoot Line Multiplier (x22) is applied to Hoot Line wins and the bet per line.

media.caption: Win with the Hoot Line feature is multiplied by 22

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95%, decisively below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€400 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a bad match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility and games with better RTP.

media.caption: Full paytable shown as multipliers of a line bet

Conclusion.text:
We do not recommend this low RTP, medium volatility forest animal-themed slot. Its RTP is simply too low for this game to be advisable.
Though cute, the cartoon animals do not make up for the poor strategy stats of this game.

title: Gold Rush (Rival)
overview:
Gold Rush (Rival)
    
        Play Gold Rush (Rival) demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Panning for gold in Gold Rush is a minimalist, Western-themed treat with an RTP of 95.94%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Set during one of the gold rushes of the 1800s, Gold Rush from Rival uses a cartoon style to draw the player into a Wild West world where the "wild" is really emphasised.
The background image is of a stream, rich in golden nuggets just waiting to be sifted out by a canny prospector. The reels are money bags and a prospecting old timer with a bushy white beard.
The Gold Rush has plenty of other games set in and around it, but this one does have some of the meditative simplicity of sitting by a river and cautiously panning for the tiny granules of gold in amongst the silt.

media.caption: Scatter win in Rival's Gold Rush slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
This slot has a pretty basic visual set up and it feels a little old fashioned in some of its design choices. However, it does manage to pull the style off.
The cartoon images and background make for a soothing world, as does the sound track, which is made up of wind soughing through the landscape.
The animations are very basic, a flashing line to indicate a win and the spin of the reels are really the only movements in frame. Whether that is charming minimalism or just boring will depend on the type of player picking up the game.

Gameplay.text:
Gold Rush is a simple three reel slot with one win line. It is as simple as it gets, so players should be ready for that kind of stripped down style.
It does manage to get in a Wild and a Scatter, which not all such small scale slots manage.
Players can also opt to play with one, two or three coins. Given the control over the coin values, players should always opt to play with three coins if possible, as this provides a proportionally larger payout on the most valuable symbol. Most times the payout for three coins is three times higher than for one coin, with the top value symbol it is four times higher.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all other symbols except the Scatter. Wins including a Wild get a x2 multiplier, with two Wilds there is a x4 multiplier.
The Scatter symbol pays out for two symbols anywhere on the winline. It pays out equal to the player’s bet per spin.
There are no bonus games, free spins, or any other special features in this slot. This is minimalist gaming at its most minimalist.

media.caption: Fairly big win with 2 Wild symbols

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.94%, more or less spot on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.01 (easily the lowest stakes we’ve seen in those currencies) up to a maximum of $/£/€30.00 per spin (which is also quite low, though will still cover most gamblers' preferred bet per spin).
Due to its age, it is hard to find details on Gold Rush’s statistical data. We were unable to find public listings for its volatility. However, with a maximum win of 400 times the player’s bet, this is certainly not a high volatility slot.

media.caption: Paytable for Rival's Gold Rush slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Overall, Gold Rush is a very pleasant game to play, with a simple gameplay mechanic and a surprisingly chilled out tone for a slot machine.
The RTP is pretty average, and the volatility isn’t high enough to really work with our slot strategies, but other players might enjoy it.
In the final analysis, Gold Rush does what it does well. But it doesn’t do much.
